On October 22, 2014 several shooting incidents occurred around [[Parliament Hill]] in [[Ottawa]]. The shootings began shortly before 10:00 [[UTC-4|EDT]] when one gunman shot and killed a [[Canadian Army]] soldier who was on ceremonial guard duty outside the [[National War Memorial (Canada)|Canadian National War Memorial]]. An additional shooting incident occurred within the [[Centre_Block#Hall_of_Honour|Hall of Honour]] at [[Centre Block]] on Parliament Hill.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Multiple|title=Soldier fatally shot outside of Parliament, one gunman killed|url=http://news.nationalpost.com/2014/10/22/soldier-shot-outside-of-parliament-at-national-war-memorial-active-shooter-believed-to-be-on-the-loose/|accessdate=22 October 2014|publisher=The National Post}}</ref>

==Shootings==
The shootings began shortly before 10:00 [[UTC-4|EDT]] on October 22, 2014, when one gunman shot and killed a [[Canadian Army]] soldier who was on ceremonial guard duty outside the [[National War Memorial (Canada)|Canadian National War Memorial]].

Earlier, two men were seen jumping out of a Toyota Corolla and running toward the National War Memorial. The perpetrators were reported to be wearing scarfs around their heads and dressed in black. One gunman was seen running with a double-barreled shotgun.<ref>[http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/10/22/us-canada-attacks-shooting-idUSKCN0IB1PY20141022 Canada's parliament attacked near where prime minister was speaking, Harper safe]</ref> The gunmen then proceeded into the [[Parliament of Canada|Canadian Parliament buildings]] where 20â€“30 shots were fired. One of the gunmen was reportedly shot dead by [[Kevin Vickers]], the [[List of Sergeants-at-Arms of the Canadian House of Commons|Sergeant-at-Arms of the Canadian House of Commons]].<ref name="CBC live">{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/parliament-hill-attacked-soldier-shot-at-national-war-memorial-in-ottawa-1.2808710|title=Parliament Hill attacked, soldier shot at National War Memorial in Ottawa|date=October 22, 2014|publisher=CBC News|accessdate=October 22, 2014}}</ref><ref name="G&M breaking">{{cite web|url=http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/politics/breaking-news-oct-22/article21217602/|title=Attack on Ottawa: Police in pursuit of multiple shooters|work=The Globe and Mail|accessdate=October 22, 2014}}</ref>

Subsequent to these initial events, Ottawa's downtown core was put under [[lockdown]], including Canada's Parliament, the [[University of Ottawa]] and the US embassy.<ref name="CBC live" /><ref name="G&M breaking" /> The [[Ottawa Police Service]] stated they, along with the [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police]], are investigating two shootings: one at the Canadian National War Memorial, and one at [[Parliament Hill]].<ref name="G&M breaking" /> Originally, police reported a third shooting that took place in the [[Rideau Centre]] at the same time. A few hours later, police corrected this mistake, saying that only two shootings took place.<ref>{{cite web|title=Soldier and assailant dead after chaotic Parliament Hill attack|url=http://www.thestar.com/news/canada/2014/10/22/one_person_shot_at_war_memorial_in_ottawa_police_say.html|website=Thestar.com|publisher=Toronto Star Newspapers Ltd|accessdate=October 22, 2014}}</ref>

The attack came a day after two Canadian Forces soldiers were struck by an [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]] sympathizer in a car, killing one of them, and after Canada raised its terror threat level from low to medium.<ref name="BBC News">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-29724907?ns_mchannel=social&ns_campaign=bbc_breaking&ns_source=twitter&ns_linkname=news_central|title=Shots fired inside Canada parliament|work=BBC News|accessdate=22 October 2014}}</ref>

==Casualties==
Ottawa hospitals reported receiving three shooting-related patients. The killed soldier was a reservist from [[Hamilton, Ontario]] and a member of the [[The Argyll and Sutherland Highlanders of Canada (Princess Louise's)|Argyll and Sutherland Highlanders]]. He was on ceremonial guard duty at the Canadian National War Memorial which includes the tomb of the unknown soldier. He was taken to hospital but succumbed to his injuries according to Government Minister [[Jason Kenney]], CTV News, and CBC News.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/hamilton/news/canadian-soldier-shot-in-ottawa-a-reservist-from-hamilton-1.2808960|title=Canadian soldier shot in Ottawa a reservist from Hamilton|date=October 22, 2014|publisher=|accessdate=October 22, 2014}}</ref>
	
A suspect was shot and killed by Kevin Vickers, the Sergeant-at-Arms of the Canadian House of Commons inside the Hall of Honour in Centre Block at Parliament.<ref name="CBC live"/>

